 want to test @WebAppConfiguration. While @WebAppConfiguration itself might not need it, to work with the web-test context bootstrap, I think it could involve loading WebTestContextBootstrapper and MockServletContext. However, if I'm using AnnotationConfigWebContextLoader, I do need spring-web and the servlet. But the existing custom AotContextLoader avoids this, and the failing test didn’t require the servlet, so maybe it’s okay!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra deterministic setup is needed: spring-test 7.0.0 declares only spring-core as a required dependency, and the existing scaffold already supplies the Spring context/JUnit/logging/assertion dependencies used by the tests. The reported failure is a version-behavior assertion mismatch, not missing service/dependency setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For the failing AOT web-resource hint coverage, account for Spring 7 behavior: @WebAppConfiguration classpath base paths are registered with recursive '**' resource patterns rather than the Spring 6 one-level '*' pattern.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"spring-test contains optional integrations for servlet/web, reactive, Mockito, TestNG, HtmlUnit, and related APIs; do not add those dependencies unless the generated test deliberately exercises those optional packages.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_038b5986762657e5016a281adb96e8819082492ceca1ef3b6b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2719, "output": 1208, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43351, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781013185877, "responseId": "resp_038b5986762657e5016a281ac2727c819098f86b9dca064173"}, "toolResults": []}
